4. Do people who live with cancer patients get vaccinated?
Caregivers and household/close contacts should be vaccinated. Since cancer patients themselves may not be as well protected by the COVID vaccine, vaccinating those around them, is especially important.

COVID Vaccines in patients with cancer. FAQ 

1. Are the vaccines safe?
Yes. There is nothing to suggest any higher risk for cancer patients.
